  "texts": [
    "Chekulayev et al.",
    "(31) discovered the \"reverse Warburg effect\" when studying the crosstalk between colon cancer cells and stromal cells.",
    "Rossi et al.",
    "(32) reported that microbial metabolites can be important regulatory factors in the TME, regulating inflammation, proliferation, and cell death in a positive or negative manner.",
    "In pancreatic adenocarcinoma, stromal-associated pancreatic stellate cells secrete alanine, which provides carbon and nitrogen for tumor cell proliferation (33)."
